                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="arkwright_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1732-92) an English businessman who invented a machine using water power for <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/spin_1#spin_sng_3" title="spinning definition"><span class="ndv">spinning</span></a> cotton, which had been spun by hand until then. He built his own factory, and became one of the early leaders of the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-industrial-revolution" title="Industrial Revolution definition"><span class="ndv">Industrial Revolution</span></a>. He was made a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/knight_1" title="knight definition"><span class="ndv">knight</span></a> in 1786.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
